$c = non_zero_random(-8,8,1);
$d = non_zero_random(-8,8,1);

while ($c**2 == 1)
{
    $c = non_zero_random(-8,8,1);
}

TEXT(beginproblem());

$showpartialcorrectanswers = 1;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Let \( f(x) = $d ? {$c} x^2\).  Then the expression
\[
    \frac{f(x + h) - f(x)}{h}
\]
can be written in the form \(Ah + Bx + C\), where \(A\), \(B\), and \(C\) are
constants.  (Note: It's possible for one or more of these
constants to be 0.)  Find the constants.
$PAR
\(A = \) \{ans_rule(5)\}
$PAR
\(B = \) \{ans_rule(5)\}
$PAR
\(C = \) \{ans_rule(5)\}
$BR
$BR
Use your answer from above to find
\(\displaystyle{\lim_{h\rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x + h) -
f(x)}{h}}\).
$BR
$BR
\(\displaystyle{\lim_{h\rightarrow 0} \frac{f(x + h) -
f(x)}{h}} = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}
$BR
$BR
Finally, find each of the following:
$PAR
\(f'(1) = \) \{ans_rule(10)\}
$PAR
\(f'(2) = \) \{ans_rule(10)\}
$PAR
\(f'(3) = \) \{ans_rule(10)\}

EOT

@answers = (std_num_cmp($c), std_num_cmp(2*$c), std_num_cmp(0),
function_cmp("2*$c*x","x"),std_num_cmp(2*$c), std_num_cmp(4*$c), std_num_cmp(6*$c));

ANS( @answers );

